	<td class="alt1">
	<!-- message, attachments, sig -->
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><u><b>Chapter 2: Battles and Bruises.</b></u> <br />
<br />
The fifth day came swifter than a griffawn closing in on its prey. During the daytime, his time was spent with Anna, creating their own adventures, both in the city and in Anna’s bedchambers. The night time was spent in Goathead’s Tavern, singing songs of glory, treasure and pleasure. In all, this had been a most wonderful time. In fact, he wished that he could stay longer. Anna had made sure he had a most pleasurable time, and working at the Goathead’s Tavern had been great as well. He longed to stay longer, but vowed to come back when this quest was over. He didn’t want to be gone from Anna too long! <br />
<br />
As he shouldered his travelers pack and instruments, he walked out the door of Anna’s house. He took one last look around to the area that he now thought of as home, and started off toward West Freeport’s Gate, and toward the West Common’s Druid Ring, where he would soon meet with Shamscale and his group of friends. He had not taken more than 10 steps when Anna’s door opened, and there stood Anna, in black leather armor, carrying her own pack. Aeleric stood there with a surprised look on his face. <br />
<br />
“Anna, what are you doing?” asked Aeleric. <br />
<br />
“Why, coming with you, hun.” answered a smiling Anna, while she walked up to Aeleric and placed a kiss upon his lips, and grabbed his hand. <br />
<br />
“But, what about your work at Goathead’s? Frederick will throw you out for leaving him like that, won’t he?” <br />
<br />
“Listen sweetie. I talked with Frederick last night before closing. All is well. He told me to keep you safe, and to bring us both back after we are done. Now stop dragging your heels, and let’s be off, we have a bit of traveling to do before sunrise is upon us.” <br />
<br />
Aeleric looked at her for another moment, then wrapped his arms around her and gave her a big hug. <br />
<br />
“I love you, you know.” said Aeleric. <br />
<br />
“Yes, I know, dear. I love you too”, said Anna. <br />
<br />
Then Aeleric started singing his song of selo and off they went, hand in hand toward the meeting with the guild, Call of the Phoenix. <br />
<br />
They reached the druid ring just as the rays of the sun were cresting the hillsides, shining on the druid’s white marble arches, casting them in a glow that seemed to emanate from the marble itself. He and Anna sat down and rested after their long trek to get here. While sitting and enjoying each other’s company, he felt a sudden buzz of energy coming from the arches of the Druid Ring. There before him, was Marriedman, Willowee, and Mommadela. <br />
<br />
“Ah, so you decided to come, and you brought your friend, I see,” said Marriedman. As if speaking to speaking to someone not there, Marriedman said, “I told you so, Sham. Now you owe me 100pp.” <br />
<br />
Aeleric looked around puzzled. Where was the Iksar at? Suddenly, the Iksar appeared a bit of a distance away from the ring and tossed Marriedman a pouch of what sounded like coins when Marriedman caught it. <br />
<br />
“Yeah, yeah. I’ll get the money back at some point or another. You can’t win them all,” Shamscale said. <br />
<br />
Mommadela walked over to Shamscale and gave the scaly Iksar a hug. “Don’t worry dear. That is coming out of your bank, not mine. I told you that he was right. But the big, bad lizzy knows all.” <br />
<br />
Shamscale threw up his arms in defeat. “Okay, whatever you all. Let’s just get this started shall we?” said Shamscale, trying his best to change the subject. <br />
<br />
Willowee introduced herself to Anna. “Don’t mind those men. They are always like that.” <br />
<br />
The rest of the group introduced themselves as well. <br />
<br />
“Nice to meet you all and I’m glad that I’m so..er…welcomed”, said Anna. “I am Anna, and not only a very good barmaid, but an exceptional rogue as well. <br />
<br />
Aeleric spoke up, “She is, too. I’ve seen first hand what those talented hands of hers can do.” <br />
<br />
The rest of the group laughed. Aeleric didn’t see what was so funny, then turning caught a glimpse of Anna. He didn’t think it possible that her face could turn red, but it was. She was flustered! But whatever for? He then realized what he had said, and how it could be misunderstood. He then turned red and embarrassed. <br />
<br />
“What I mean is her roguish skills are good”, he said. <br />
<br />
Shamscale chuckled. “Well glad to have you with us, Anna. I’m sure your talents will be appreciated.” He snickered. <br />
<br />
Mommadela hit him playfully upside the head. “Keep it up Scaly, and you’ll be needing your pet to keep you warm”. <br />
<br />
“OUCH!” Shamscale said in mock pain. He rubbed the back of his head where she had hit him. “Just because I have scales, doesn’t mean that doesn’t hurt, you know.” <br />
<br />
They all laughed at that. <br />
<br />
“Okay, let’s get serious for a bit” said Shamscale. “Let me explain the quest and what is involved. Basically there was an incident and several creatures were released by the Lesser Gods that be, into the lands of Norrath. The Lesser Gods placed Questgivers here in Norrath to have adventurers go around and collect evidence that these creatures are dispatched. The evidence is then brought back to the Questgivers, and then we get the elixir. Simple.” <br />
<br />
Marriedman interrupted. “You forgot one thing, Shamscale”. He turned to Aeleric and Anna. “These creatures assumed various forms to hide themselves from the Gods. There are 10 different forms that they took. The Lesser Gods just can’t wipe these races from the world for this would cause the Almighty Gods to take notice of this, which would cause much displeasure and the wrath of the Almighty Gods upon those Lesser Gods that allowed this to happen. They have then turned to us regular mortals to clean up their mess, as we hunt and kill through these lands anyway, and so would not cause undo notice. And so the Lesser Gods have placed the task of chosen individuals to hunt for the escaped creatures and return with evidence of them being eliminated from this world. This is the journey that we will be on. From the Questgivers, we have learned that the items can be identified as having a ‘collector’s stamp’ upon them. That will be how to tell them apart from the other creatures they have put themselves in with.” <br />
<br />
Shamscale continued. “We have not been told where to look, specifically, for each creature, but we have been given riddles to where they are. Mommadela, if you would, please read what the riddle is, for the benefit of Aeleric and Anna.” <br />
<br />
Mommadela was already rummaging around in her pack. “Here it is”, she said and pulled out a rolled up parchment. <br />
<br />
Mommadela unrolled the parchment and began to read. <br />
<br />
<blockquote><div align="center">“Questor: Below is a listing of riddles <br />
to where the escaped creatures may <br />
be found. Only if you are successful <br />
at solving the riddles and finding the <br />
creatures, then you may seek the much <br />
sought reward that few will get. <br />
<br />
These conflicted strands are a badge of honor. <br />
This pouch is crafted from finer things than leather. <br />
Weigh your options before seeking these. <br />
A crumbling intellect can be a burden. <br />
It towers above, but these help it grow below. <br />
The rhyme of the mountains. <br />
Cursing can be heard whenever this is used. <br />
Their bark is the least of your worries. <br />
Fans the swarming flame. <br />
Grown from the seeds of failure.”</div></blockquote></div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
