	<td class="alt1">
	<!-- message, attachments, sig -->
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>“Now”, said Shamscale, “we have figured out from talking with others that are on this quest, that bloodgill scales go to the riddle, ‘weigh your options before seeking these’. ‘It towers above, but these help it grow below’ belong to Burynai Excavators. ‘Their bark is the least of your worries’ can only refer to the Drolvarg mutts in Firiona Vi. ‘Fans the swarming flame’ must mean those giant hornets in Burning Woods. ‘Cursing can be heard whenever this is used’, we believe, are Iksar Witch Doll that Goblin Witchdoctors have. ‘Rhythm of the mountains’ refer to the Mountain Giant Tumps in Frontier Mountains. ‘Pouch from finer things than leather’ refers the the silk dropped by Drachnids in the Dreadlands. We are unsure of the others though. They have to be off creatures in areas we have not covered that are in Kunark, though. <br />
<br />
Anna spoke up then. “Well, if I remember my time hunting some in The Overthere, Sarnak War Braids that some Sarnaks carry around can be collected and given to the local militia give much honor to the individual. That may be what ‘conflicted strands are a badge of honor’ is mentioning”. <br />
<br />
Marriedman smacked himself in the head. “Why didn’t I catch that?” <br />
<br />
Willowee snickered. Too busy playing with your pet, maybe?” <br />
<br />
That got a laugh out of all of them, turning Marriedman’s face red. “Very funny, Hun. Very funny.” <br />
<br />
Aeleric thought a moment, then spoke. “What about the brittle skulls that the iksar skeletons have in the Field of Bones? Would that be the ‘crumbling intellect can be a burden’? <br />
<br />
“Good catch, Aeleric”, said Mommadela. “Well, that leaves ‘seeds of failures’ and ‘pouch of finer things than leather’.” <br />
<br />
Shamscale thought for a bit. “Wait a second. I remember reading about the frogloks in Swamp of No Hope from an ancient tome kept in the Shaman Guild in Cabilis. It talked of how the frogloks tried to raise up against the Iksarian Empire, but failed and was only able to retain their hold in the Swamp. That was where the name of the swamp came from. ‘Swamp of No Hope’. Maybe it is talking about No Hope Swamp Moss.” <br />
<br />
They all considered what Shamscale had said. “You may be right, Sham” agreed Marriedman. “A bit of a reach, but so are the rest of these. I just wish that they could just tell us where these things are, but then they, along with all the other quest givers, seem sadistic in nature. They love to play their little games. At least this quest gives a good reward!” <br />
<br />
They all nodded in agreement. “True”, said Willowee. “The riddles are very cryptic, but the reward is indeed worth it.” <br />
<br />
She then turned to Mommadela. “Well, Momma. Is it time to fly the friendly skies?” <br />
<br />
Mommadela looked up. “Sure thing. Just writing the last of the clues’ solutions down.” She rolled up the parchment and tucked it back into her pack, and re-shouldered it. “Okay, everyone gather close and get ready. Teleport to Planes of Knowledge incoming.” <br />
<br />
They all gathered round Mommadela as she began to cast her teleportation spell. In the next instance, they were all standing in Planes of Knowledge, barraged with the yells of people asking for Kodiac’s Endless Intellect, Hand of Virtue, and a slew of other beneficial spell castings. <br />
<br />
Shamscale spoke up. “Okay. We will start in Field of Bones first, then to Kurn’s Tower. From there to Warslik Woods, to The Overthere, Frontier Mountains, and then to Lake of Ill Omen. From there, Mommadela can port us back up to here, then we will take the stone back to Cabilis and head into the Swamp of No Hope, Firiona Vi, Dreadlands, and then finally into Burning Woods.” <br />
<br />
With everyone differing to Shamscale as their leader, and following his direction, they ran to the Cabilis Stone, and off to collect the items needed for the completion of the quest and the final reward from a pleased QuestGiver. <br />
<br />
The fun and adventure they had and the battles they encountered throughout the Kunarkian Empire brought them all closer as friends, and before the journey was over, both Aeleric and Anna were inducted into the Guild. As they went from area to area, the group of friends left behind them a trail of slaughter. None of the Collector’s creatures that had hidden were spared. During this time, Aeleric’s spellsong abilities and that of Anna’s roguish abilities were put to good use. Thanks to Aeleric’s songs, no one seemed ever to tire nor run out of mana. And Anna was key to keeping the Dragoons from attacking the group while they were hunting the Sarnaks in The Overthere, as well as sneaking stealthly through the Froglok City in Swamp of No Hope, looking for frogloks having the moss in their possession. <br />
<br />
This is not to say that there were not hardships as well. During the battling with the Burynai Excavators in the basement of Kurns Tower, Aeleric had fallen down into some subterranean cavern underneath Kurns Tower. He had been surrounded by Burynai there and was about to be finished off, but that had ended shortly with the rest of the group slaughtering every Burynai that had drew breath in that cavernous area. Anna had led the charge to save him, and the murderous rage at the thought of harm coming to Aeleric had led her. She had killed dozens of the furry oversized rodents to get to him and protect him while Mommadela worked her healing magic into him. He would have died from his wounds had it not been for Mommadela’s healing touch and Willowee’s comforting spells. <br />
<br />
Shamscale almost bought it when the group were fighting a mass rush of Drolvargs and a scouting party of Elven Warriors came upon him. Shamscale went from fighting Drolvargs to fighting several Elven Warriors as well. If not for the quick actions of Willowee pacifying the warriors, and then Mommadela shouting to the scouting party that Shamscale was not their enemy, Shamscale would have had to slay the Elven Warriors as well, which would not have bodded well with Mommadela’s kin, who were still very apprehensive to their union. <br />
<br />
There was also trouble when they had entered into Dreadlands and been attacked by hordes of Drachnids. Willowee had been taken to one of the main nests, and it took all their skills and resources to get to her and escape with their lives. <br />
<br />
Into the seventh day, however, they had finally completed their questing, and had received their reward of the Elixir of Scholarship. They all headed to Goathead’s Tavern to celebrate. Frederick was so happy to see Anna and Aeleric again that he shouted that all drinks for the night were on the house. This brought a much pleased cheer from the patrons, as it was a very rare thing for the grumpy Dwarf to even give a free round, much less than a a whole night of free drinks! Aeleric and Anna decided to settle back down in Freeport, working for Frederick, but assured Shamscale and the rest of their group that, if called upon, they would gladly help out their new guildmates. With happy and tearful goodbyes, Shamscale, Mommadela, Marriedman, and Willowee left late in the night for their own destinations. Helping clean up the tavern, Aeleric looked over to where Frederick was cleaning the mugs, and then to where Anna was sweeping the floor. He caught her eye, and she smiled brightly and blew him a kiss. ‘Yep’, he thought. ‘I’ve found my place at last. I shall wander no more.’</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
